  <summary>3/19/1997--Introduced.
IRA Self-Loan Act - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow loans to be made or secured by an individual retirement account for first-time homebuyer expenses, education expenses, or medical emergency expenses. Exempts such loans from the tax on prohibited transactions.</summary>
